texts.text: >After so many cases,
>the Liberators came to befriend and bond with some number of demons.
>This is a tale about a little incident that happened
>between the Liberators and these demons.
>You walk into the Hideout...
Boss... Boss!
Kabuso... What is it?
I'm busy writing the set list for my next show.
But boss... Do you even have that many songs to pick from...?
What was that...?
Nothing! Please ignore what I just said!
I wanted to say...! I did some training and got a little stronger!
And I wanted you to see the results, Boss...
Hmm... Okay then. Show me.
Yeah! Check it out!
Tadaaï½ž!
It's everyone's favorite idol, Shionyan!
So what's different than usual...?
B-but! Really?! Please look closer...!
Isn't this your regular outfit?!
It's not that.
I mean even a little kid can change their own clothes, right?
I-it might be easy for you, boss,
but it's not just about changing clothes...
Getting it this right was really hard!
It's not like I even wear clothes to begin with...
So in the end all you did was claim you got stronger?
But boss...! This has to be useful somehow...!
My transformation skills got better! Right?!
Yeah, okay. It's great.
Aww, boss...!!
>You leave the living room as Kabuso and Shionyan keep up their banter...
>You walk into the Church of False Gods...
>Vagit usually is there to greet you but...
Hey...!
Privyet, Dx2!
This place exists at... At... Uhh...
Uh oh... I forgot the rest...
A-anyways! Welcome to the Church of False Gods!
What are you doing here?
Where's Vagit?
I'm here to help Vagit!
He's in the back researching something about a new ritual...?
Why are you here? The usual?
The sacred ceremony of... Demon Fusion is what you seek...?
>You wonder if it's safe to ask Nadja to handle any Fusions...
Well, what'll it be?
Nadja, what are you doing? Oh...
Privyet, Dx2.
My apologies. I was in the back looking into something and didn't realize...
What can I do for you today, comrade?
I'm here for Fusion.
The usual.
Understood. Preparations have already been made.
I never knew you liked those kinds of demons this much.
Now, what kind of demon would you...?
I want to help! What can I do?
Nadja, there's nothing...
No! You always say that and make me leave!
I'll be good, so please let me help a little!
*Sigh*
This isn't a game. Please leave us alone for a bit.
No... H-hey wait!
Don't push me!
I want to help...!!
>The Church's doors close shut...
My apologies.
What's the matter? Please don't give me that look.
About your Fusion. What did you have in mind?
>You leave the Church of False Gods and return to the living room.
*Wince*
*Gasp*
>You bump into Jack the Ripper...
Sorry.
Watch where you're going!
It's nothing...!
No, you watch it!
Crap! Just hurry up and let me go!
This much commotion...

*Groan*
When did I fall asleep...?
N-newbie? When did you get here?
Shit!!
You pillock! There goes my best chance!
Ugh! If it weren't for you...!
That just mucked up all of my plans!
I kept quiet all this time, so you'd let your guard down!
Goddamnit...!!
>Jack the Ripper runs off...
Jack the Ripper? Yo, why's he all salty?
I guess he's always like that. Rika's assassin defense it always 100% too.
Rika and Newbie... And Shionyan's over there.
How 'bout we meet up where Shionyan is?
I'm just gonna get right to it.
There's somethin' we need to investigate. First...
>A few days later...
Yes, me too. It was something like a handgun...
You too, Rika? It was my stage outfit. I need it for my next show.
Vagit?
A catalyst for a new ritual I was testing.
It's not big and hardly looks like anything expensive.
What's up?
Problem?
Just looking for a few things... We all seem to have misplaced stuff.
Rika's gun. My new stage outfit.
And Vagit's catalyst for a new ritual.
If it were only that we misplaced them...
Nadja, Kabuso and Jack the Ripper have also been absent for a few days now.
I'll ask anyways... Have you seen any of those three?
>Come to think of it, you haven't seen any of those three for a while...
I guess that's a no for Newbie.
Us three losing things coinciding with those three demons disappearing.
They might be connected...
We don't have any other leads, so we can start looking for them to start.
I'll help.
But where?
Thanks.
That's the thing...
I'm having Meat Balloon also look for Kabuso.
Any ideas where Nadja and Jack the Ripper went?
Oh, I might know someone that can help.
You, Pixie!
W-what is it?
You're the one that's always hanging out with Nadja, yes?
Y-yeah... How did you know?
Don't mind that... Call it an educated guess.
Your friend... Do you know where Nadja is?
Nadja... She came to my forest about two days ago.
Oh...
Comrades, would it be alright if we look for Nadja first?
That's our best lead at the moment, so I don't see why not.
I agree.
Horosho. Would you mind guiding us to your forest?
